      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "Cynics might argue that some of the Biden officials and lawmakers participating in the legislative and regulatory push are motivated not by principle, but by a desire to avoid blame and damage their partisan opponents. That may be entirely true — but that’s a feature, not a bug.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "type": "callout",
        "calloutEmoji": "💡",
        "calloutText": "Follow us on <a href=\"https://apple.news/TeRci1RtoQfWCNA5h7NTBlg\"><strong>Apple News</strong></a> and <a href=\"https://news.google.com/publications/CAAqBwgKMPvKngswktW2Aw\"><strong>Google News</strong></a> to make sure you see our stories first, and to help make sure others see our breaking news as well.",
        "backgroundColor": "blue"
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "American democracy is predicated on the theory that different factions will engage in ruthless and messy competitions to show who is most responsive to voters’ demands — and that such competitions will ultimately produce positive results, regardless of the amorality and opportunism of the individual players.",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "This process is most often short circuited by political corruption and by a corporate media that shields rather than scrutinizes power — both of which almost always ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "children": [
              {
                "detail": 0,
                "format": 0,
                "mode": "normal",
                "style": "",
                "text": "cut voters out of the game",
                "type": "text",
                "version": 1
              }
            ],
            "direction": "ltr",
            "format": "",
            "indent": 0,
            "type": "link",
            "rel": null,
            "target": null,
            "title": null,
            "url": "https://act.represent.us/sign/problempoll-fba/",
            "version": 1
          },
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": ".",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          }
        ],
        "direction": "ltr",
        "format": "",
        "indent": 0,
        "type": "paragraph",
        "version": 1
      },
      {
        "children": [
          {
            "detail": 0,
            "format": 0,
            "mode": "normal",
            "style": "",
            "text": "But despite that corruption and despite the media’s best efforts to ",
            "type": "text",
            "version": 1
          },
